Supreme Court, Appellate Term, September, 1897.

Before Daly, P. J.; McAdam and Bischoff, JJ.

Emily L. Hamilton, Respondent, v. William F. Howe et al., Appellants. —Appeal from judgment of the General Term of the City Court affirming a judgment in favor of plaintiff. David May (Joseph Koch, of counsel), for appellant. Adelbert E. Carroll, for respondent.

Judgment affirmed, with costs, upon argument.
